<style>
  .carde {
    transition: box-shadow 0.9s ease;
    border: 2px solid transparent;
  }

  .carde:hover {
    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 128, 0, 0.5);
    border-color: #008000;
  }
</style>
<div style="height:570px">
  <div class="container p-3 ">
    <div class="carde text-center rounded shadow bg-white">
      <div class="card-body d-flex w-100">
        <div class="row w-100">
          <div class="col-md-6"> <!-- Apply Bootstrap's column class -->
            <canvas data-controller="chart"
              data-chart-chartdata1-value="<%= @chartdata1.to_json %>"
              data-chart-chartdata2-value="<%= @chartdata2.to_json %>"
              data-chart-chartdata3-value="<%= @chartdata3.to_json %>"></canvas>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6"> <!-- Apply Bootstrap's column class -->
            <h1 class="carde-title mt-3">Your Report</h1>
            <% @report.simulation %>
            <p>Your daily consumption <%= @report.daily_consumption %> Wh/day</p>
            <p>The solar kit proposed has a
              <%= render partial: "power", locals: { report: @report } %></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container mt-3">
  <p class="text"> <a href=""><i class="fa-solid fa-triangle-exclamation" style="color: #63E6BE;"></i></a> Please take a note although we have provided results and options for solar kits on our website, it's important to understand that these results are not final. Your ultimate choice may necessitate further information to  suit your unique  geographic area or your requirements and preferences.</p>
  </div>
  </div>
  <div class="container">
  </div>
</div>
